    },
    [
      "p",
      {
        "className": "lesson-meta"
      },
      "Lesson 38"
    ],
    [
      "h1",
      {},
      "The Interjections"
    ]
  ],
  [
    "article",
    {},
    [
      "section",
      {},
      [
        "p",
        {},
        "Interjections (Επιφωνήματα) are words that express sudden emotions\n            or reactions. They are often used in spoken Greek to add color and\n            feeling to a conversation."
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "interjection-grid mt-8"
        },
        [
          "div",
          {
            "className": "card "
          },
          [
            "ul",
            {
              "className": "inter-list"
            },
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Μπράβο!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "Bravo! / Well done!"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Α μπά!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "No way! / Don't tell me!"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Άντε! / Άιντε!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "Come on! / Let's go!"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Αχ!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "Oh! / Ah! (pain or sigh)"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Μακάρι!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "I wish! / Hopefully!"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Αλίμονο!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "Alas! / Unfortunately!"
              ]
            ],
            [
              "li",
              {},
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "greek"
                },
                "Εύγε!"
              ],
              [
                "div",
                {
                  "className": "meaning"
                },
                "Excellent! / Bravo!"
              ]
            ]
          ]
        ]
      ],
      [
        "div",
        {
          "className": "info-box  mt-12 mb-12"
        },
        [
          "h3",
          {},
          "Cultural Highlight: \"Άντε\""
        ],
        [
          "p",
          {},
          [
            "strong",
            {},
            "Άντε"
          ],
          " ",
          "is one of the most common words in Greece. Depending\n                on the tone, it can mean \"Come on\", \"Let's go\", \"Hurry up\", or even\n                \"Get out of here!\" (in disbelief)."
        ]
      ]
    ]
